<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-063-056 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 309 047</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Sept 9 1991 n658 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>HDTV: the game's the thing. (high definition television) (1992Olympics)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Woolnough, Roger.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>European broadcasting and electronics companies are hoping thattheir coverage of the 1992 Olympics games in Spain will be a goodadvertisement for high definition television (HDTV) technology.andO;Some analysts have expressed doubt though, as to whether Europe'ssatellite television broadcasting companies will be ready to usethe D2-Mac transmission standard for programs.andP;  The standard isthe precursor to the full HD-Mac system that is designed todeliver true HDTV images to the home user.andP;  ITT has recentlyreleased the HDMA2290 digital signal processor, which someanalysts believe could form the basis of a HD-MAC decoder.andP;  Someanalysts believe only a few functions have now to be integratedinto the low-cost integrated circuit technology that will be usedin HDTV technology.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   ITT Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   ITT HDMA2290 (Digital signal processor) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     High-Definition TelevisionFuture TechnologiesEuropeBroadcastingStrategic PlanningSemiconductor IndustryProduct IntroductionDigital Signal ProcessingMicroprocessors.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Decoding Europe's HDTV signals. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>